Name: Butter
Subtitle: NA
Tip: Keep butter in its original packaging or in a covered dish to prevent it from absorbing odors from other foods. For longer storage, you can wrap it in aluminum foil or place it in an airtight container.

Name: Buttermilk
Subtitle: NA
Tip: Pour buttermilk into an ice cube tray or airtight container, leaving some headspace for expansion as it freezes. This is perfect for using in recipes later.

Name: Cheese
Subtitle: hard such as cheddar, swiss, block parmesan
Tip: For long-term storage, wrap hard cheese tightly in plastic wrap and then in aluminum foil before freezing to preserve its quality.

Name: Cheese
Subtitle: parmesan; shredded or grated
Tip: Store grated parmesan in a glass container or a tightly sealed plastic bag to minimize exposure to air. You can also add a layer of plastic wrap directly on the surface before sealing the container to keep it fresh longer.

Name: Cheese
Subtitle: shredded; cheddar, mozzarella, etc.
Tip: Freeze shredded cheese in small portions wrapped in plastic and then placed in a resealable freezer bag. Use as needed without defrosting the entire amount.

Name: Cheese
Subtitle: processed slices
Tip: Keep  in its original packaging if it's resealable, or transfer it to a plastic bag and press out the air before sealing. You might also place a paper towel in the bag to absorb moisture.

Name: Cheese
Subtitle: soft such as brie, bel paese, goat

Name: Cream cheese
Subtitle: NA
Tip: Keep cream cheese in its original foil wrapping if unopened. Once opened, wrap tightly in plastic wrap or store in an airtight container to prevent it from drying out.

Name: Eggs
Subtitle: in shell
Tip: Store eggs in their original carton rather than the fridge door, as the temperature tends to be more constant in the main part of the fridge. This helps maintain freshness and minimizes odor absorption.

Name: Milk
Subtitle: plain or flavored
Tip: Store milk at the back of the fridge where it’s colder, rather than the door, which is subjected to warmer air when opened. Keep the container closed tightly.

Name: Yogurt
Subtitle: NA
Tip: Store yogurt in its original container with the lid tightly closed in the coldest part of the refrigerator. Avoid frequent temperature changes to maintain its quality.
